Extremely impressive android app version of the classic RPG. I didn't have high hopes when I downloaded but was willing to risk the three bucks. Once it was installed I opened and was immediately impressed. I do highly recommend using a wireless controller and tablet to fully appreciate this awesome game. I use a Steelseries controller designed specifically for mobile gaming and I literally spent four hours last night totally re hooked on this game. Bug free too as far as I can tell!

It's amazing to come back and play this game 20 years later and still be blown away by how fun it is, I don't normally play games on my phone but this actually made me go out and buy a Bluetooth controller

Very swish port with good touch controls and great performance, and one fatal flaw - input latency. The natural imprecision of controlling an FPS with touch controls, plus some noticeable lag from input to movement, in a title that is well known for being rather punishing in its difficulty at the best of times, makes for a pretty frustrating play. Technically I can't fault the port, though. The game is still fun and irreverent.

Playing on a phone can be hard, but this was game got me to develop the patience and skill to successfully use virtual joy sticks. That being said it's next to impossible on anything higher than medium difficulty. But that's no shade on the actual port, this one is fantastic.

This is a very fun, and complete game, with a purpose. No comparison with 
those expensives and repetitive fremium scams dominating Android and iOS 
stores. The controls take some time to master, but that's how game were 
back then. even though playing with controller and has definite enhanced my 
experience it is an excellent game either way. Thank you developers for 
bringing this jewel to mobile and for your honesty on charging just once 
for the game and not scamming people with in app purchases like most people 
now.

Lots of content, super fluid gameplay and very challenging. It will scratch 
that old school fps itch and then some. Take a minute to customize the 
touch controls before playing , trust me it will make a big difference. 
Just as fun and frantic as you would expect from a doom or nuke clone only 
with the added bonus of actually being ad good as , and different enough 
from, it's aforementioned big brothers. And the price is that of a ninja in 
a room full of priceless artifacts. A steal.

Amazing port, the touch controls *are* a little unwieldy, but I like it

Honestly it's one of the best games I've ever played on my phone. The 
controls took me a lil bit to get the hang of but after I got past that the 
game has been a complete blast, this is coming from someone who usually 
hates mobile games too. Now all we need is Duke Nukem, Blood, Doom 1&2 to 
be released for mobile and Ill be one happy camper.

I'm happy to see this classic on android and the price makes it a bit of a bargain.  The touch controls make it hard to manuever without accidentally firing weapons and for explosives that can be a problem.  Gameplay and layout is true to the original enough that game guides will get you through but lots of graphic elements have been changed, enough so that it's not a faithful reproduction of the original games.  Easier than an engine frontend but a lot is lost for that simplicity.

The game controls require a lot of tweaking to make it really playable but it gets the job done. However I'm running into an issue in Level 3 of the base game in Master Leep's temple where I need to run forward across a descending hallway to finish the level where the hallway keeps falling either too fast to reach the other end or my character is just running too slow because it's impossible to progress any further from there. I've tried various ideas to get across but nothing works and after watching gameplay of the PC version I'm convinced this part may be bugged. Also really random instant deaths would occur if I collide with certain areas in the environment even though it's safe to grab the items they have.
